##Cloud Computing
On Demand delivery of IT resourcesover the internet with pay-as-you-go pricing.


##Difference between On-premise and Cloud Provider??
ON PREMISE- own servers
          - hire IT people
          - Pay real estate
          - Take Risk

CLOUD     - Someone else owns the resources
          - Someone else hires IT people
          - someone else pays for the real estate 
          - No risk of customer


##Why choose cloud provider over on-premise?
- pay-on-demand 
- sharing cost with the customers
- stop guessing capacity
- Increase speed and agility
- No maintaining of data centers
- Go global in mins.

